edu.ucla.sspace.graph

Interface TypedEdge<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Edge
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    DirectedTypedEdge<T>, WeightedDirectedTypedEdge<T>, WeightedTypedEdge<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    SimpleDirectedTypedEdge, SimpleTypedEdge, SimpleWeightedDirectedTypedEdge, SimpleWeightedTypedEdge

    public interface TypedEdge<T>
extends Edge
    An interface for edges in multigraphs. In a multigraph, two vertices v1 and v2 may have mulitple edges between then provided that the for any two edges !e1.equals(e2).

    This interface allows for a multigraph to have mutliple types of edges that extend from a common type. For example, a graph that represents cities may contain edges indicating the different types of transportation (e.g. car, train, bus) between two cities, where those types each have their own subtypes (e.g., airline carrier, bus company, etc.)

    See Also:
    Multigraph
